
### Operating System and Active Directory Week 1 — User & Group Management

Date: March 31, 2026
Tool: Windows Server 2022 & Windows 11 VMs

Tasks Completed
* Created three Organizational Units: IT, HR, and Sales.
* Provisioned three domain user accounts with specific logon names.
* Created a Global Security Group named 'All_Staff_Group'.
* Nested all three departmental users into the security group.
* Verified domain connectivity and user permissions by logging into Windows 11.
* Decommissioned test objects to maintain lab hygiene.

Key Concepts
* `Active Directory Users and Computers (ADUC)`: The primary interface for object management.
* `Organizational Units (OUs)`: Containers used to organize objects and link Group Policies.
* `Security Groups`: Objects used to assign permissions to multiple users simultaneously.
* `Domain Authentication`: The process of a client machine validating credentials against a Domain Controller.

Lessons Learned
* Effective organization in AD simplifies administrative tasks as the environment scales.
* Testing the end-user experience is a vital part of the provisioning process.

